1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,360
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:06,360
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:08,880
My name is Katherine and welcome everyone.
我是Katherine，欢迎大家。

4
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:11,440
Today we've got an elementary level lesson for you.
今天我们为大家准备了一节初级课程。

5
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:14,640
It's all about sending things through the mail.
内容是关于通过邮寄寄送物品。

6
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:15,640
That's right.
没错。

7
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:17,600
So maybe gifts, maybe letters.
可能是礼物，也可能是信件。

8
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:22,100
We're going to the post office so why don't we jump right into this dialogue.
我们要去邮局，所以不如直接进入这段对话吧。

9
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:32,780
Let's listen to it for the first time and we'll be right back.
我们先听一遍，然后马上回来。

10
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:36,660
Hi I would like to send this package to China and these postcards as well.
你好，我想把这个包裹寄到中国，还有这些明信片。

11
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:37,660
Very well.
好的。

12
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:40,860
You will need some stamps for the postcards and I need to weigh that package too.
明信片需要贴邮票，我还得称一下那个包裹。

13
00:00:40,860 --> 00:00:41,860
Great.
太好了。

14
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:43,460
How much is this going to cost?
这要花多少钱？

15
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:44,460
Well it depends.
嗯，这要看情况。

16
00:00:44,460 --> 00:00:47,900
Do you want to send it via priority, express or standard mail?
您想用优先、快递还是标准邮寄？

17
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,100
What's the difference?
有什么区别？

18
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:51,940
Well standard mail can take up to 15 working days.
标准邮寄最多需要15个工作日。

19
00:00:51,940 --> 00:00:55,740
Priority is a bit faster and will arrive in about 5 to 8 working days.
优先邮寄快一些，大约5到8个工作日到达。

20
00:00:55,740 --> 00:00:58,460
Express is the fastest but it's also the most expensive.
快递是最快的，但也是最贵的。

21
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:01,540
It only takes three days and you can track your package online.
只需三天，你就可以在线追踪包裹。

22
00:01:01,540 --> 00:01:02,540
I see.
我明白了。

23
00:01:02,540 --> 00:01:03,900
Well there's no rush.
嗯，不急。

24
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:05,980
Please send it via priority mail.
请用优先邮件寄送。

25
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:07,100
Please be extra careful.
请格外小心。

26
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:13,580
The contents of the package are fragile.
包裹里的物品是易碎的。

27
00:01:13,580 --> 00:01:15,100
All right so pretty simple dialogue.
好的，这个对话很简单。

28
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:18,020
We want to send a package through the mail.
我们想通过邮寄寄一个包裹。

29
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:28,140
So why don't we take a look at some of those mail related terms in Language Takeaway.
那么，我们来看看“语言要点”中一些与邮件相关的术语吧。

30
00:01:28,140 --> 00:01:32,260
Alright so the first item we're going to talk about in today's Language Takeaway is something
好的，今天“语言要点”中我们要讨论的第一个项目是

31
00:01:32,260 --> 00:01:33,540
you can send.
你可以寄送的东西。

32
00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:35,300
It's called a postcard.
它叫明信片。

33
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,300
A postcard.
明信片。

34
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:41,860
Okay so very popular among people who are traveling and they want to send a postcard
好的，这在旅行的人中非常流行，他们想寄一张明信片

35
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:42,860
back home.
回家。

36
00:01:42,860 --> 00:01:43,860
That's right.
没错。

37
00:01:43,860 --> 00:01:49,620
So a postcard is something that you usually buy at a tourist destination like Walt Disney
所以明信片是你通常在旅游景点买的，比如沃尔特·迪士尼

38
00:01:49,620 --> 00:01:51,260
World for example.
世界。

39
00:01:51,260 --> 00:01:54,540
And it has a picture on the front and some words on the back.
它正面有图片，背面有文字。

40
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:57,500
So you can write a letter on the back of this picture.
所以你可以在图片背面写信。

41
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,860
So it's very simple.
所以这很简单。

42
00:01:59,860 --> 00:02:00,960
It's not really a letter.
这其实不算是信。

43
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,740
You don't put it in an envelope.
你不用把它放进信封里。

44
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:06,860
You just write whatever you want on the back of the postcard.
你只需在明信片背面写任何你想写的内容。

45
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:10,900
But you do have to put a stamp on it in order to send it.
但你必须贴上邮票才能寄出去。

46
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:11,900
That's right.
没错。

47
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:12,900
So stamp is our next word.
所以邮票是我们的下一个词。

48
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,940
A stamp comes in different price ranges.
邮票有不同的价格范围。

49
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:19,940
That means that some stamps are more expensive than other stamps.
这意味着有些邮票比其他邮票更贵。

50
00:02:19,940 --> 00:02:23,580
This is like money for the mail.
这就像邮件的钱一样。

51
00:02:23,580 --> 00:02:29,700
So you have to buy the stamps and in order to prove that you have paid for the letter
所以你必须买邮票，为了证明你已经为你想寄的信付了钱，

52
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:33,660
that you want to send, you must place the stamps on the letter on the envelope or on
你必须把邮票贴在信上、信封上或

53
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:34,660
the postcard, right?
明信片上，对吧？

54
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:38,100
So depending on the size and weight, it costs more.
所以根据大小和重量，费用会更高。

55
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,100
That's right.
没错。

56
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:44,140
And usually you lick a stamp to place it on the card so it doesn't fall off.
通常你会舔一下邮票，然后贴在卡片上，这样它就不会掉下来。

57
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,140
True.
确实。

58
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:46,140
That's right.
没错。

59
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:47,140
You gotta lick it.
你得舔一下它。

60
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,140
Alright.
好的。

61
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:50,420
So as we talked about, a package can be a letter, a postcard.
正如我们之前谈到的，包裹可以是信件或明信片。

62
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:56,380
You place stamps on it and we need to weigh the package to know how much money we have
你在上面贴邮票，我们需要称重包裹才能知道要付多少钱。

63
00:02:56,380 --> 00:02:57,380
to pay.
付钱。

64
00:02:57,380 --> 00:02:58,380
That's right.
没错。

65
00:02:58,380 --> 00:03:02,620
So sometimes a package is very heavy if it's filled with books for example.
所以有时候包裹很重，比如里面装满了书。

66
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:06,820
Sometimes it's very light if it's filled with clothes or feathers.
有时候很轻，比如里面装满了衣服或羽毛。

67
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:11,340
And so to find out how much something weighs, we have to weigh it.
为了知道某物有多重，我们必须称它。

68
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:12,340
This is a verb.
这是一个动词。

69
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,340
Okay.
好的。

70
00:03:13,340 --> 00:03:14,340
So this is a verb, right?
所以这是一个动词，对吧？

71
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,340
To weigh.
称重。

72
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:20,780
So you want to know how many kilos or how many pounds this item has.
所以你想知道这个物品有多少公斤或多少磅。

73
00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:21,780
Right.
对。

74
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:25,860
So we could say, it weighs a lot or how much do you weigh?
所以我们可以说，它很重，或者你多重？

75
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:26,860
Okay.
好的。

76
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:27,860
Things like this.
诸如此类。

77
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:28,860
Very good.
很好。

78
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:29,860
Alright.
好的。

79
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:34,140
Moving on, we have the different types of mailing speeds, I guess, right?
接下来，我们有不同类型的邮寄速度，对吧？

80
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:39,220
So we saw three, via priority mail, express mail or standard mail.
所以我们看到了三种：优先邮件、快递邮件或标准邮件。

81
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:40,220
So let's go in parts.
所以我们分部分来讲。

82
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,100
Let's go with the first one, via priority mail.
我们先讲第一个，通过优先邮件寄送。

83
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,980
Priority is fast.
优先就是快。

84
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:47,220
It means priority is something that's important.
它意味着优先是重要的东西。

85
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:49,740
So I have many priorities at work.
所以我在工作中有很多优先事项。

86
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:51,440
This means they're important.
这意味着它们很重要。

87
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,440
Very important.
非常重要。

88
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,980
So this letter has a certain importance.
所以这封信有一定的重要性。

89
00:03:54,980 --> 00:03:58,980
It's a little bit more important than for example, the other letters.
它比其他信件稍微重要一点。

90
00:03:58,980 --> 00:03:59,980
That's right.
没错。

91
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:03,320
But express is the most important, the fastest.
但特快是最重要的，最快的。

92
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:05,900
So something that's express is fast.
所以特快的东西就是快的。

93
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:09,580
Like an expressway is the fast highway.
就像高速公路是快速公路。

94
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:10,580
Express mail.
特快邮件。

95
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:11,580
Okay.
好的。

96
00:04:11,580 --> 00:04:13,260
So express mail is the fastest.
所以特快邮件是最快的。

97
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:17,780
And now the normal cheapest mail is standard mail.
而现在最便宜的普通邮件是标准邮件。

98
00:04:17,780 --> 00:04:18,780
Standard.
标准。

99
00:04:18,780 --> 00:04:24,260
So the word standard usually means the average or the normal mail.
所以“标准”这个词通常意味着平均或普通邮件。

100
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:27,020
And in this case, it usually takes the longest.
在这种情况下，它通常花的时间最长。

101
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,020
Okay.
好的。

102
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:30,980
So obviously standard mail is the cheapest.
所以显然标准邮件是最便宜的。

103
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:34,940
Express mail is the most expensive because it's the fastest.
特快邮件是最贵的，因为它最快。

104
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:35,940
That's right.
没错。

105
00:04:35,940 --> 00:04:37,220
So we've got all of those speeds.
所以我们有所有这些速度选项。

106
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:41,740
Now let's listen again to today's dialogue and try and listen for the words we just talked
现在让我们再听一遍今天的对话，试着听出我们刚才讨论的词汇，

107
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:47,540
about and we'll be back in a moment to talk about some important phrases.
我们稍后会回来讨论一些重要的短语。

108
00:04:47,540 --> 00:04:54,580
Hi, I would like to send this package to China and these postcards as well.
你好，我想把这个包裹寄到中国，还有这些明信片。

109
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,580
Very well.
好的。

110
00:04:55,580 --> 00:04:58,740
You will need some stamps for the postcards and I need to weigh that package too.
明信片需要贴邮票，我还得称一下那个包裹。

111
00:04:58,740 --> 00:04:59,740
Great.
太好了。

112
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:01,380
How much is this going to cost?
这要花多少钱？

113
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:02,380
Well it depends.
嗯，这要看情况。

114
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:05,820
Do you want to send it via priority, express or standard mail?
你想通过优先、特快还是标准邮件寄送？

115
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:06,820
What's the difference?
有什么区别？

116
00:05:06,820 --> 00:05:09,860
Well, standard mail can take up to 15 working days.
嗯，标准邮件最多需要15个工作日。

117
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:13,700
Priority is a bit faster and will arrive in about five to eight working days.
优先邮件快一点，大约五到八个工作日到达。

118
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:16,420
Express is the fastest but it's also the most expensive.
特快是最快的，但也是最贵的。

119
00:05:16,420 --> 00:05:19,500
It only takes three days and you can track your package online.
只需要三天，而且你可以在网上追踪包裹。

120
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,500
I see.
我明白了。

121
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,860
Well, there's no rush.
嗯，不着急。

122
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,940
Please send it via priority mail.
请通过优先邮件寄送。

123
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:30,460
Please be extra careful, the contents of the package are fragile.
请特别小心，包裹里的东西易碎。

124
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:37,460
Alright we're back so now let's take a look at three key phrases on Fluency Builder.
好了，我们回来了，现在让我们看看流利度构建器上的三个关键短语。

125
00:05:37,460 --> 00:05:38,460
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

126
00:05:38,460 --> 00:05:43,500
Alright, so the first phrase today is one that I like to use a lot.
好的，今天第一个短语是我很喜欢用的一个。

127
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:46,980
We say, it depends.
我们说，这要看情况。

128
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,300
How much is this going to cost?
这要花多少钱？

129
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:50,340
Well, it depends.
嗯，这要看情况。

130
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:53,020
So the phrase could be, it depends.
所以这个短语可以是“这要看情况”。

131
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:54,700
So it depends.
所以“这要看情况”。

132
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:56,180
When do you usually use this?
你通常什么时候用这个？

133
00:05:56,180 --> 00:06:02,260
Okay, if you ask me a question, I can have one answer but maybe there's another possible
好的，如果你问我一个问题，我可能有一个答案，但也许还有另一个可能的

134
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:03,540
answer.
答案。

135
00:06:03,540 --> 00:06:07,380
For example, what are you going to wear tomorrow, Marco?
比如，马可，你明天穿什么？

136
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:09,700
It depends if it rains or not.
这要看下不下雨。

137
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:11,380
Okay, it depends.
好的，这要看情况。

138
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:15,540
If it rains, I will wear a raincoat.
如果下雨，我就穿雨衣。

139
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:19,920
If it's sunny, I will wear a normal coat.
如果晴天，我就穿普通外套。

140
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:26,460
So it depends means there is a situation or a circumstance that might change and if it
所以“这要看情况”意味着有一种情况或环境可能会改变，如果它

141
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:28,100
does, my answer will change.
变了，我的答案也会变。

142
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,900
Right, so it is a conditional, it depends.
对，所以这是一个条件句，这要看情况。

143
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:34,160
For example, I can ask you, what are you going to eat tonight?
比如，我可以问你，你今晚吃什么？

144
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,700
It depends.
这要看情况。

145
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:41,420
If I exercise, I'm going to have a hamburger and if I don't exercise, I'll have a salad.
如果我锻炼了，我就吃汉堡；如果没锻炼，我就吃沙拉。

146
00:06:41,420 --> 00:06:42,620
Nice, okay.
不错，好的。

147
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:44,080
So it depends.
所以“这要看情况”。

148
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:49,300
Now we have another phrase when they were talking about how long it's going to take
现在我们还有另一个短语，当他们讨论寄东西需要多长时间时

149
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:50,940
to mail something.
用到的。

150
00:06:50,940 --> 00:06:55,620
He said standard mail can take up to 15 working days.
他说标准邮件最多需要15个工作日。

151
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:59,020
So we have this little phrase there, up to.
所以我们有这个短语，“最多”。

152
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:00,020
Up to.
最多。

153
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:04,820
So up to, when you hear this, these two words together, that's an indication, it's a sign
所以“最多”，当你听到这两个词连在一起时，这是一个提示，一个标志，

154
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:08,380
that we're talking about the maximum, the most.
表示我们在谈论最大值，最多。

155
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:13,900
Okay so tomorrow, the temperature might go up to 24 degrees Celsius.
好的，所以明天温度可能高达24摄氏度。

156
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:17,300
Okay so the temperature maximum will reach 24.
好的，所以最高温度会达到24度。

157
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,500
It could be maybe 22, 21.
可能是22度、21度。

158
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,500
But not 25.
但不会是25度。

159
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,500
Not 25.
不会是25度。

160
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:23,300
No, because up to means the top.
不会，因为“最多”意味着上限。

161
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:25,300
So you're usually dealing with numbers, right?
所以你通常处理的是数字，对吧？

162
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:29,020
For example, this coat can cost up to $150.
例如，这件外套最高可以卖到150美元。

163
00:07:29,020 --> 00:07:33,660
Wow, so the most I will spend is $150.
哇，所以我最多花150美元。

164
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:38,740
So sometimes you have a number like this when we're talking about sending a package.
所以有时候在讨论寄包裹时，你会遇到这样的数字。

165
00:07:38,740 --> 00:07:43,460
We can send packages that weigh up to 10 kilos.
我们可以寄重量不超过10公斤的包裹。

166
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:45,300
Not more than 10 kilos though.
但不能超过10公斤。

167
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:46,900
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

168
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:52,020
And now for our last phrase to close off the dialogue, the guy said, well you know what,
现在来看我们最后一句短语来结束对话，那个人说，嗯，你知道吗，

169
00:07:52,020 --> 00:07:53,020
there's no rush.
不着急。

170
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:54,020
No rush.
不着急。

171
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:55,020
There's no rush.
不着急。

172
00:07:55,020 --> 00:07:59,180
Okay, well the first word we want to look at here is the word rush.
好的，我们首先要看的词是“rush”。

173
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:02,740
In this case, we're talking about sending a package and the postcard, right?
这里我们在讨论寄包裹和明信片，对吧？

174
00:08:02,740 --> 00:08:05,780
So does this person want it to arrive fast?
所以这个人希望它快点到吗？

